        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Wedderburn rented a hunting lodge at Rhifail, Sutherland (a county in the Highlands of Scotland) in 1870. The keeper has not been identified. Wedderburn was probably hunting with <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_6384.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Claudius William Bell</ref> and <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_6559.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">William Edwin Price</ref> (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_8244.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Wedderburn 1884</ref>, p. 128).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD discussed stags’ fighting in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1966.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi></ref> 2: 240.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3"><ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1966.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi></ref> 2: 103.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">CD added this anecdote to <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1967.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi> 2d ed.</ref>, p. 407.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f5"><hi rend="italic">Muscicapa griseola</hi> is now <hi rend="italic">Muscicapa striata.</hi></note>
        </div>        
            
